<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<topic id="e084673a-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2" revisionNumber="1">
	<developerConceptualDocument
	  xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5"
	  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

		<introduction>
			<para>
				The Double Agent control can operate in three different modes: <token>connected</token>, <token>standalone</token>, and <token>contained</token>. The mode a developer chooses
				depends on the application&#39;s requirements.
			</para>
		</introduction>


		<section address="connected">
			<title>
				<token>connectedUc</token> Mode</title>
			<content>
				<para>
					<token>connectedUc</token> mode is the control's default mode, and is compatible with <token>MsAgent</token>. In this mode, the Double Agent control acts as a gateway to the Double Agent server. The control
					provides all of its services through it's connection with the server. It automatically connects to the
					server as required, and releases the connection when it's no longer needed.
				</para>
				<para>
					When operating in <token>connected</token> mode, all of the control's characters belong to
					the <legacyItalic>server</legacyItalic>. This means that all client applications share a <legacyItalic>single</legacyItalic> copy of the character's
					<link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Character">window</link>,
					<link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Menu">
						<token>PopupMenu</token>
					</link>, <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Icon">
						<token>NotificationIcon</token>
					</link>, <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Balloon">
						<token>WordBalloon</token>
					</link>, <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#ListeningTip">
						<token>ListeningTip</token>
					</link>, speech engines, etc.
				</para>
				<para>
					Other server resources such as the <link xlink:href="e08466be-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">
						<token>AdvancedCharacterOptions</token>
					</link> window and the <link xlink:href="e0846717-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">
						<token>VoiceCommands</token>
					</link> window
					are also shared by all client applications.
				</para>
				<para>
					If the control is contained in a form, it will <legacyItalic>not</legacyItalic> be visible at run-time.
				</para>
				<para>
					A character window floats on top of all application windows and is <legacyItalic>not</legacyItalic> visually associated with
					a specific client application. It can produce Text-to-Speech output and receive mouse, keyboard, and
					Speech Recognition input even if the client application's window is inactive (not in the foreground)
					or disabled. It can even be used by a client application that has no visible window.
				</para>
				<para>
					The <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Balloon">
						<token>WordBalloon</token>
					</link>, the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#ListeningTip">
						<token>ListeningTip</token>
					</link>, and the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#VoiceCommands">
						<token>VoiceCommands</token>
					</link> window
					are also <legacyItalic>topmost</legacyItalic> windows, and the <token>ListeningKey</token>
					is always available.
				</para>

			</content>
		</section>

		<section address="standalone">
			<title>
				<token>standaloneUc</token> Mode</title>
			<content>

				<para>
					In <token>standalone</token> mode, the Double Agent control is <legacyItalic>not</legacyItalic> connected to
					the Double Agent server. It provides the server's functionality directly.
				</para>
				<para>
					When operating in <token>standalone</token> mode, all of the control's characters belong
					to the <legacyItalic>control</legacyItalic>. Since the control runs in the same process as the client application, this
					means that the client application has it's own private copy of its characters and all of their resources.
					The control also has its own copy of the <link xlink:href="e08466be-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">
						<token>AdvancedCharacterOptions</token>
					</link> window and the <link xlink:href="e0846717-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">
						<token>VoiceCommands</token>
					</link> window.
				</para>
				<para>
					If the control is contained in a form, it will <legacyItalic>not</legacyItalic> be visible at run-time.
				</para>
				<para>
					A character window floats on top of the application window containing the Double Agent control, but <legacyItalic>
						not
					</legacyItalic> other application windows. It is visually associated with your client application as an <legacyItalic>
						owned <token>Popup</token>
					</legacyItalic> of the control's parent window - that is, it's hidden when the
					control's parent window is minimized. However, the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Icon">
						<token>NotificationIcon</token>
					</link> remains visible.
				</para>
				<para>
					The <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Balloon">
						<token>WordBalloon</token>
					</link>, the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#ListeningTip">
						<token>ListeningTip</token>
					</link>, and the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#VoiceCommands">
						<token>VoiceCommands</token>
					</link> window
					are also <legacyItalic>
						owned <token>Popup</token>s
					</legacyItalic> of the control's parent window, and the
					<token>ListeningKey</token> is available only when your application is in the foreground.
				</para>

			</content>
		</section>

		<section address="contained">
			<title>
				<token>containedUc</token> Mode
			</title>
			<content>

				<para>
					In <token>contained</token> mode, the Double Agent control is a <legacyItalic>visible</legacyItalic> child window
					of it's containing form. Like <token>standalone</token> mode, the control is not connected
					to the server and it's characters are owned by the client application. Unlike <token>standalone</token>
					mode, the character is not a floating window; it's displayed within the control's child window.
				</para>
				<para>
					<token>containedUc</token> mode applies to a <legacyItalic>single</legacyItalic> character of a control that's operating
					in <token>standalone</token> mode. The control can load multiple characters, but only one
					can be contained. When there is a <token>contained</token> character, the control will be
					visible. If there is no <token>contained</token> character, the control will <legacyItalic>not</legacyItalic>
					be visible.
				</para>
				<para>
					The <token>contained</token> character is set by the client application at run-time, so the
					control can dynamically change to and from <token>contained</token> mode. Also, even when
					there's a <token>contained</token> character, other characters can be shown as floating (uncontained)
					windows.
				</para>
			</content>
		</section>

